    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A variation of Art Nouveau in France, coined by architect Hector Guimard to describe his own style. Guimard was known for his Paris Métro entrances made of steel and glass and the term is often used in conjunction with "Style Métro.”</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
